283
00:21:24,949 --> 00:21:36,320
As the bank is creating this two hundred thousand dollar loan to me the customer they're doing two things from an accounting perspective on the asset side of their books.

284
00:21:37,020 --> 00:21:37,981
They have an asset.

285
00:21:38,021 --> 00:21:44,747
Now the bank has an asset which is that promissory note that says I owe you two hundred thousand dollars plus interest.

286
00:21:45,028 --> 00:21:46,249
That's something that the bank

287
00:21:47,009 --> 00:21:50,410
counts on its books as real money, as an asset, right?

288
00:21:50,690 --> 00:21:55,211
They can go to court and they can go after me and get the $200,000, right?

289
00:21:55,911 --> 00:21:59,372
But on the liability side, what's the bank liable for?

290
00:21:59,732 --> 00:22:07,253
They just created a bank account for me and they deposited $200,000 in it so I can actually buy the house or buy the car or start the business or whatever.

291
00:22:07,673 --> 00:22:14,255
So what they've done is start from zero and increase their liabilities and their assets by $200,000 at the same time.

292
00:22:16,213 --> 00:22:17,834
which means their books are still balanced.

293
00:22:18,294 --> 00:22:29,778
Now tell me what's stopping them from making that loan instead of 200,000, making it 300,000, 500,000, nothing in terms of the mechanics of creating the loan.

294
00:22:30,179 --> 00:22:38,942
But their responsibility is not just to inflate the value of my loan and let me buy the most expensive house that I can't afford their job.

295
00:22:39,522 --> 00:22:40,963
And that's their responsibility.

296
00:22:41,003 --> 00:22:45,865
That's why they have a banking license and they're regulated is to serve the public purpose, which is to,

297
00:22:46,486 --> 00:23:00,049
