439
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:30,623
If they're brought to you by super PACs, then we don't have a democracy.

440
00:34:30,963 --> 00:34:34,125
We don't have a government of the people by the people for the people.

441
00:34:34,145 --> 00:34:36,567
We have a government of the super PACs for the super PACs.

442
00:34:37,302 --> 00:34:45,090
And that's really the crux of the MMT approach, that it's not just a technical kind of economic policy program.

443
00:34:45,411 --> 00:34:51,257
It shines the light on the institutional structure of the economy.

444
00:34:51,618 --> 00:34:55,001
And that institutional structure includes politics, includes the legal framework.

445
00:34:55,362 --> 00:34:58,145
That's why we call them lawmakers, because they make the laws.

446
00:34:58,625 --> 00:34:58,845
right?

447
00:34:59,125 --> 00:35:08,011
And if we are not going to be able to redesign the system to be more equitable, to be more sustainable, unless we redesign the institutional mechanism.

448
00:35:08,632 --> 00:35:13,555
So there's no way to avoid the political fight in this.

449
00:35:13,635 --> 00:35:22,821
And what we're trying to do in the MMT community is educate, empower, inform people so that they can mobilize to push back against those

450
00:35:23,745 --> 00:35:35,871
structures, because otherwise, we literally don't have a democracy, which means we're not going to afford a Green New Deal with an oligarchy in charge of how government finances operate.

