459
00:36:05,979 --> 00:36:14,804
I mean, look at Japan, almost three decades of massive quantitative easing and large fiscal deficits and no inflation.

460
00:36:15,265 --> 00:36:18,887
They actually have deflation, right, which is the main problem that they have.

461
00:36:19,362 --> 00:36:21,844
And Japan, for decades, the U.S.

