532
00:42:19,481 --> 00:42:33,915
Higher education inflation has been happening over the last two or three decades, primarily because of spending cuts from states that normally support state universities, state schools.

533
00:42:34,395 --> 00:42:40,581
So when those schools receive fewer dollars from state authorities, they have to raise tuition.

534
00:42:41,142 --> 00:42:42,303
And by raising tuition,

535
00:42:42,705 --> 00:42:48,187
They open the floodgates for private schools to raise their tuition, too, because they're in the same market.

536
00:42:48,387 --> 00:42:48,587
Right.

537
00:42:48,967 --> 00:42:50,628
So that's that's element number one.

538
00:42:50,668 --> 00:42:51,648
It's not the only thing.

539
00:42:52,048 --> 00:42:58,870
