00:43:01,691 --> 00:43:04,372
So when we have health care price inflation,

542
00:43:04,848 --> 00:43:07,850
higher education also gets more expensive, just like any other business, right?

543
00:43:08,170 --> 00:43:20,356
Which is why a Medicare for All program would reduce the cost of health care for all businesses, including universities, and lower the cost of even private school education, not just state schools.

544
00:43:20,977 --> 00:43:30,522
Number three, universities over the last three decades, especially private schools, have been competing for students with nicer buildings and swimming pools and gymnasiums.

545
00:43:30,582 --> 00:43:32,363
And so cost of construction

546
00:43:33,839 --> 00:43:34,959
is massive.

547
00:43:35,080 --> 00:43:38,582
Cost of heating and cooling buildings is massive.

548
00:43:38,843 --> 00:43:43,486
So when you decarbonize, when you produce renewable energy, you're also reducing that cost.

549
00:43:44,027 --> 00:43:49,011
And when you reduce the cost of healthcare on construction companies, well, guess what?

550
00:43:49,471 --> 00:43:51,513
The cost of construction will also go down.

551
00:43:51,793 --> 00:43:53,554
So all of these things are intertwined.

552
00:43:54,215 --> 00:44:00,620
And what we've been doing over the last three decades is pushing that burden on families.

